{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nDocument the code-health surface for client adoption. No novel architecture (T1) — this is documentation of the shipped surface.\n\n## Grounded facts (E4 — verified via Grep/Read; drives what gets documented)\n- VERIFIED `grep -n \"^\\\\[project.optional-dependencies\\\\]\" pyproject.toml` + the block: today the extras are mcp/reviewbot/ui/agents/eval/tracing/grounding/grounding-t2/dev — there is NO `metrics` extra yet; it is ADDED by ticket 9597 (depends chain) and contains ONLY `lizard`.\n- scc and jscpd are EXTERNAL PATH CLIs, NOT pip deps and NOT in the extra (consistent with the grounding extras own comment: \"scc/lizard ... are external CLIs, not pip deps\").\n- VERIFIED `test -f tests/scripts/test_metrics_docs.py` — it already exists (ticket 121b) with a narrower contract; this ticket EXTENDS it without breaking existing assertions.\n- `docs/config.md` is the canonical config reference (`head -1 docs/config.md` = \"# rebar configuration — design of record (ADR) + reference\").\n\n## Approach (G6)\nDocument the three-part adoption (`pip install rebar[metrics]` for lizard + `scc` on PATH + `jscpd` on PATH) in the existing docs, and extend the existing docs test rather than adding a parallel one. Rationale: single source of truth, and the pinned docs-test is the enforcement point.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] reuse-surface documents the analyzer seam + `[metrics]` extra (lizard) + scc/jscpd as separate PATH prereqs. PROVE: `grep -Eq \"metrics\\\\]\" docs/reuse-surface.md && grep -q \"scc\" docs/reuse-surface.md`.\n- [ ] `docs/config.md` documents every `[code_health]` key with type + default. PROVE: `grep -q \"\\\\[code_health\\\\]\" docs/config.md`.\n- [ ] user-guide documents the three-part install + \"no analyzer -> Unavailable\" behavior. PROVE: `grep -q \"rebar\\\\[metrics\\\\]\" docs/user-guide.md`.\n- [ ] The existing + new assertions pass. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/scripts/test_metrics_docs.py` (green: pre-existing 121b assertions AND the new metrics-surface assertions).\n\n## Dependencies: 0734 (content prerequisite; relates_to recorded).\n## Files: docs/reuse-surface.md, docs/config.md, docs/user-guide.md, AGENTS.md, tests/scripts/test_metrics_docs.py (extend)\n## Scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784533539235612001,"uuid":"0ba326de-af15-40fb-bbc3-375b79ce5f55"}